## Screen 7: Shrine / Respawn Screen

**Route:** Modal overlay on death OR `/shrine` on shrine node visit
**Purpose:** Respawn, manage travel, optional upgrades.

```
┌────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│              🌸 RIVER SHRINE               │
│           Chapter 1 — Edo Streets          │
├────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│                                            │
│   You were defeated.                       │  ← Only shown on death
│   Respawned at nearest shrine.             │
│   No items lost.                           │
│                                            │
├────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│   HP fully restored ✓                      │
│   Barrier fully restored ✓                 │
│   Resource fully restored ✓                │
├────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│   SHRINE OPTIONS                           │
│                                            │
│   [⚔️ Return to Battle]                    │  ← Go back to last node
│   [🗺 Return to Map]                       │  ← Back to world map
│   [🚀 Fast Travel...]                      │  ← Opens shrine teleport list
│   [🛒 Shrine Merchant — Buy Consumables]   │  ← Optional
│                                            │
├────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│   DISCOVERED SHRINES (Fast Travel)         │
│                                            │
│   ● River Shrine — Edo Streets (Here)      │
│   ● Forest Gate Shrine — Dark Forest 🔒    │  ← Not yet unlocked
│                                            │
│   [Close]                                  │
└────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

### Notes for developer
- Shrine screen is always a modal overlay, not a full route replacement.
- On death: shown automatically with "defeated" message.
- On shrine visit: shown without defeat message.
- Fast travel list comes from `useMapStore` discovered shrines array.
- Locked shrines shown but greyed out; show region name + 🔒 icon.

